sql:
SELECT battery_type, battery_capacity
FROM sensor_batteries
WHERE battery_type = 'lithium-ion';

SELECT level
FROM battery_levels
WHERE level_date >= '2023-01-01';

SELECT battery_type, SUM(battery_capacity) AS total_capacity
FROM sensor_batteries
GROUP BY battery_type;

SELECT sensor_id, status, status_date
FROM sensor_status
WHERE status = 'inactive';

external_knowledge:
- "running low on energy" refers to a battery level less than 50%; 
- "power reservoirs" refers to the average battery levels; 
- "life signs" refers to sensor readings; 
- "at least one recorded vital sign" refers to the condition that a sensor must have recorded at least one reading; 
- "a spark of energy left" refers to the condition that a sensor must have at least some battery level recorded, i.e., average battery level > 0.

sql:
SELECT battery_id, AVG(level) as average_battery_level
FROM battery_levels
GROUP BY battery_id;

SELECT MAX(download_date) AS latest_failed_download
FROM data_downloads
WHERE download_notes LIKE 'Failed download%';

external_knowledge:
- Sensor activation refers to the point in time when a sensor becomes operational and starts recording data;
- 'timeline of events' refers to a chronological record of all activities related to a sensor, including status changes, access logs, and maintenance history;
- 'comprehensive view' refers to a complete and detailed understanding of sensor performance and usage over time.
